         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">9/5/88 ¶  ¶ It does not seem to me, dear Mr Macdonald, that we here could approach either the R.G.S. of London or the Imperial Government on Mr Bevan's behalf  ¶ directly ¶ , as he was  ¶ not ¶   ¶ ou...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">88.05.09</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Alexander Macdonald</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A38 Royal Geographical Society of Australasia (Vic. Branch) papers, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">9/5/88</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It does not seem to me, dear Mr Macdonald, that we here could approach either the R.G.S. of London or the Imperial Government on Mr Bevan's behalf <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">directly</hi>
               </seg>, as he was <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">our</hi>
               </seg> emissury.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I cannot see how a recommendation, that his companions should or ought to <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">share</hi>
               </seg> in any reward, could be rendering the reward useless to him, as <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">he</hi>
               </seg> would get the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">main-portion</hi>
               </seg> of it.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See T. Bevan to M, 4 May 1888, and notes thereto.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Poor Hartmann, Hunstein, Denton and many others never received anything for such discoveries, as they made by their private means and sacrificed their lives.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Of course we are anxious to see Mr Bevan rewarded, but we can <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not</hi>
               </seg> single him out individually and overlook every one else; nor can we support a specified claim from here, as the extent of reward should be fixed<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>fixed <seg style="font-style: italic; ">above</seg> recommended <seg style="font-style: italic; ">deleted</seg>.</p>
               </note> by the Governor of New Guinea and the Home Government. Dr W. Macgregor is sure to be consulted anyhow by the Secr. of State for the Colonies on such a subject. In accordance with the wish of the Council I wrote a letter of felicitation to H Exc Dr M'Gregor,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to W. MacGregor, 7 May 1888 (in this edition as 88-05-07a).</p>
               </note> also an unofficial letter to Sir Edw Strickland,<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
               </note> asking him to favor us in the Bevan case with fuller information. Copies of both letters are in my copying book here.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Can you still kindly supply one or two copies of new publication.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Not identified. See M to A. Macdonald, 7 May 1888.</p>
               </note> I shall make good use of them.</p>
         </div>
